      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems from NAFEMS and ASME V&V 10 suite reproduced to within 1% of analytical solutions; patch-test passed for all element types used.",
      "rationale": "Each FEA code verified against standard benchmark problems covering linear elasticity, contact, and large-displacement regimes relevant to pedicle screw bending. Patch tests and manufactured-solution checks confirm correct implementation. Gradation 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates < 2% change in peak von Mises stress and construct stiffness between medium and fine meshes; Richardson extrapolation applied.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted on the screw-rod interface and screw shank regions of highest stress gradient. Richardson extrapolation yields GCI < 1.8% for stiffness QoI and < 2.1% for peak stress. Discretization error adequately characterised at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
