      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals < 1e-6; direct solver cross-check performed on coarse mesh; contact penetration < 0.001 mm.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear Newton-Raphson iterations converged to force residual < 1e-7 in all load steps. Contact penetration monitored and maintained below tolerance. Direct solver used for verification on representative sub-model. Exceeds Gradation 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup, boundary conditions, and load application; documented simulation plan reviewed prior to execution.",
      "rationale": "Simulation plan peer-reviewed by independent analyst not involved in model construction. Boundary condition application (fixed inferior vertebral body, applied moment at superior body) verified against ASTM F1717 fixture geometry. No use errors identified. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening validated against coupon data; contact formulation captures screw-rod interface behaviour; geometric nonlinearity included.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material modelled with bilinear isotropic hardening; modulus and yield stress calibrated from manufacturer coupon tests. Augmented Lagrange contact with friction coefficient 0.2 captures clamp-load behaviour. Large-displacement formulation active. Model form appropriate for quasi-static bending regime. Gradation 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certified coupon tests on same lot material; geometry from calibrated CMM measurements; torque preload from calibrated torque wrench records.",
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry digitised via CMM to ±0.01 mm; material properties from three-replicate tensile coupons per ASTM E8; set-screw torque preload 6 Nm per manufacturer IFU and recorded per test. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (n=500). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from same production lot; dimensional inspection confirms within-spec geometry; traceability to lot certificates maintained.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from single production lot; CMM inspection of all screws and rods confirms dimensional conformance. Two-laboratory split (6+5) provides inter-laboratory reproducibility data. Sample size supports Gradation 3 per ASME V&V 40 Table."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least two independent load levels or fixture configurations tested; environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) recorded and controlled.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at single load configuration (ASTM F1717 standard fixture, 10 mm offset, room temperature). Environmental conditions recorded but only one test condition evaluated, preventing multi-condition coverage. Achieves Gradation 2 only; falls below required Gradation 3. Accepted under risk-informed rationale with compensating factors in other areas."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs mapped one-to-one to measured experimental parameters; any unmeasured parameters justified by sensitivity analysis showing < 5% influence on QoI.",
      "rationale": "Systematic mapping table produced linking each FEA input to corresponding experimental measurement. Friction coefficient and polyethylene block stiffness not directly measured; sensitivity analysis shows combined influence < 3% on stiffness QoI. Equivalency confirmed at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric (mean error, RMSE) computed with uncertainty bounds; statistical equivalence test applied; visual comparison of force-displacement curves provided.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute percentage error 7.2% for stiffness and 6.8% for yield load across N=11 constructs; RMSE within experimental standard deviation. Two-sample t-test confirms no statistically significant difference (p=0.31). Force-displacement curve overlay shows good morphological agreement. Gradation 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (construct stiffness, yield load, peak von Mises stress) directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements; traceability matrix provided.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary ASTM F1717 acceptance metrics and directly inform fatigue life prediction for 510(k) submission. Peak von Mises stress links to fatigue failure mode. Traceability matrix maps each QoI to a clinical risk and regulatory requirement. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
